After serving for a time in the military (about 18 years old)I went to South Lebanon as a rifleman in UNIFIL (93-94)  While I was there I saw death and terror in a way I had never experienced. <br>
Up until then I did'nt really consider myself mortal at all. These things made me realize that I could die at any given moment<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hrp --><img src=http://heartjoys.fcpages.com/Sparrow'sHearth/harp.gif ALT=":hrp"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> (not a very happy thought).  When I came home I decided that I would find out what kind of God I had met down there. Bcause that was the clear impression I had. So I started reading about all kinds of religion budhism, islam, Bahai, hindu, etc<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :intel --><img src=http://heartjoys.fcpages.com/Sparrow'sHearth/znaika.gif ALT=":intel"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . This went along for a couple of years. Until I came to the conclusion that the Bible had the answer. So therefore I started praying and going too church.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :g6 --><img src=http://heartjoys.fcpages.com/Sparrow'sHearth/g6.gif ALT=":g6"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
(the norwegian lutheran church). The last couple of years has been good to me. I'm married and we have two kids. I also have a calling now too become a priest, so now I'm studying theology. And I hope that contact with you people out there will give me a new perspectives and help deepen my relationship with God. <br>
